T1  - Impact of myo-inositol treatment in women with polycystic ovary syndrome in assisted reproductive technologies.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1186/s12978-021-01073-3
A1  - Merviel, Philippe
A1  - James, Pandora
A1  - Bouee, Sarah
A1  - Le Guillou, Mathilde
A1  - Rince, Camille
A1  - Nachtergaele, Charlotte
A1  - Kerlan, Veronique
Y1  - 2021//
Y2  - 20210119//
N2  - Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) is marked in 30 to 40% by insulin resistance and hyperandrogenism. Myo-inositol (MI) increases insulin sensitivity, decreases hyperandrogenism and improves the menstrual cycle. Its effect during assisted reproductive technologies (ART) has been studied by many authors. We conducted a review of the literature on the impact of MI administration in PCOS women in assisted reproductive technologies. Myo-inositol is effective in normalizing ovarian function, improving oocyte and embryo quality in PCOS, however further evaluations by large multicentre randomized controlled trials are needed to assess the clinical pregnancy and live birth rates in ART.
