T1  - Comparison of the efficacy between NAC and metformin in treating PCOS patients: a meta-analysis.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1080/09513590.2019.1689553
A1  - Song, Yu
A1  - Wang, Huimin
A1  - Huang, Hongli
A1  - Zhu, Zhengyan
Y1  - 2020//
Y2  - 20191121//
N2  - Our aim is to evaluate the clinical effectiveness and safety by comparing N-acetyl-cysteine (NAC) with metformin administrated by polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) patients. Systematic review and meta-analysis of randomized clinical trials (RCTs). MEDLINE, EMBASE, Web of Science and China National Knowledge Infrastructure were searched for studies. 10 studies were considered eligible for inclusion. NAC significantly reduced BMI and total testosterone, there was no significant difference in pregnancy rate, serum LH level, fasting insulin, and LH/FSH ratio. In conclusions, NAC may be considered as an alternative supplement to metformin, but large-scale randomized controlled trials are needed to assess the efficacy and safety of NAC in PCOS patients.
